<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>BAAM Review Audit · {{business_name}}</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Archivo:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&family=Instrument+Serif:ital@0;1&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@300;400;500;700&family=Noto+Serif+TC:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>{{{styles}}}</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ====================== PAGE 1 — COVER + SECTION 1 ====================== -->
<section class="page">
  <header class="doc-header">
    <div class="doc-header-left">
      <div class="doc-header-brand">BAAM · Review Audit</div>
      <div class="doc-header-sub">{{doc_header_subtitle_left}}</div>
    </div>
    <div class="doc-header-right">
      <div><strong>Vol. I · No. 001</strong></div>
      <div>Prepared {{audit_date_display}}</div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="cover-hero">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">A personalized diagnostic · {{page_count_display}} pages · for the owner, not the developer</div>
    <h1 class="cover-title">The reputation report you've been <em>missing.</em></h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">Where your business stands today, what it costs you each month, and the five things to do in the next 12 months.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <div class="cover-meta-label">Business</div>
      <div class="cover-meta-value">{{business_name}}{{#if business_name_secondary}}<br><span class="mono" style="font-size:13px; color:var(--ink-mute);">{{business_name_secondary}}</span>{{/if}}</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <div class="cover-meta-label">Location</div>
      <div class="cover-meta-value">{{business_address_line_1}}<br><span class="mono" style="font-size:13px; color:var(--ink-mute);">{{business_address_line_2}}</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <div class="cover-meta-label">Vertical</div>
      <div class="cover-meta-value">{{vertical_display_name}}<br><span class="mono" style="font-size:13px; color:var(--ink-mute);">{{vertical_subtype}}</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <div class="cover-meta-label">Audit ID</div>
      <div class="cover-meta-value mono" style="font-size:18px;">{{audit_id}}<br><span style="color:var(--ink-mute); font-size:11px;">prepared by BAAM Studio</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hook-quote">
    <p>Average businesses become <em>hot and popular</em> by building reviews relentlessly.<br>Excellent businesses become <em>invisible</em> because they ignore them.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="ornament">§</div>

  <div class="section-marker">
    <span class="section-marker-num">§ 01</span>
    <span class="section-marker-title">Why Reviews Decide Who Wins</span>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-headline">The rules of getting found <em>changed.</em></h2>
  <p class="section-deck">Five things that are now true about local search — each measured, each cited, none arguable.</p>

  <div class="fact-grid">
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-num">01</div>
      <div class="fact-stat">16–20<span class="unit">%</span></div>
      <div class="fact-body">Of Google's Local Pack ranking weight now comes from review signals — up from ~11% five years ago. The share rises every year.</div>
      <div class="fact-source">Whitespark · 2026 Local Ranking Factors</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-num">02</div>
      <div class="fact-stat">81<span class="unit">%</span></div>
      <div class="fact-body">Of consumers use Google for local reviews. It's the only major platform whose usage is rising — Yelp, Facebook, and BBB are all declining.</div>
      <div class="fact-source">BrightLocal · 2026 Local Consumer Review Survey</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-num">03</div>
      <div class="fact-stat">+25<span class="unit">%</span></div>
      <div class="fact-body">Conversion lift from a single 0.1-star rating increase in brick-and-mortar businesses. The 4.0 threshold is binary — 70% of consumers filter by it.</div>
      <div class="fact-source">Uberall · via BrightLocal</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-num">04</div>
      <div class="fact-stat">5–9<span class="unit">%</span></div>
      <div class="fact-body">Revenue increase per 1-star rating bump. Causal, not correlational. Independent businesses see the upper end of this range; medical and legal even higher.</div>
      <div class="fact-source">Luca · Harvard Business School</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact" style="grid-column: span 2;">
      <div class="fact-num">05</div>
      <div class="fact-stat" style="font-size:42px;">AI search now reads your reviews.</div>
      <div class="fact-body" style="max-width:680px;">ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, and Google's AI Overviews pull directly from review content and ratings to answer "best [service] near me" questions. Without strong reviews, AI will literally not mention you when a customer asks.</div>
      <div class="fact-source">Google Transparency Report · 2024–2026</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="closing-line">Excellence isn't enough anymore. <em>Visibility</em> decides who walks through your door.</p>

  <div class="doc-footer">
    <span>BAAM Review Audit · {{business_name}}</span>
    <span>Page 01 / {{page_count_display}}</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ====================== PAGE 2 — SECTION 2 SNAPSHOT ====================== -->
<section class="page">
  <header class="doc-header">
    <div class="doc-header-left">
      <div class="doc-header-brand">BAAM · Review Audit</div>
      <div class="doc-header-sub">§ 02 · Your Current Snapshot</div>
    </div>
    <div class="doc-header-right">
      <div><strong>{{business_name}}</strong></div>
      <div>{{business_address_line_2}} · {{audit_date_display}}</div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="section-marker">
    <span class="section-marker-num">§ 02</span>
    <span class="section-marker-title">Your Current Snapshot</span>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-headline">Where customers <em>actually look</em> for you.</h2>
  <p class="section-deck">Free tier covers Google — by itself ~81% of local consumer reach. The paid audit adds Yelp, Facebook{{#if is_paid}}, Zocdoc, Healthgrades{{/if}}.</p>

  <table class="snapshot-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Platform</th>
        <th>Rating</th>
        <th>Reviews</th>
        <th>Last Review</th>
        <th>Profile Health</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <div class="platform-name">
            <div class="platform-icon">{{snapshot_google.icon}}</div>
            <div>
              <div class="platform-meta-strong">{{snapshot_google.name}}</div>
              <div class="platform-meta-sub">{{snapshot_google.meta_sub}}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </td>
        <td><div class="star-rating">{{{snapshot_google.rating_stars_html}}} <span class="mono" style="font-size:15px;">{{snapshot_google.rating_value}}</span></div></td>
        <td><div class="review-count">{{snapshot_google.review_count}}</div></td>
        <td><div class="last-review{{#if snapshot_google.last_review_is_stale}} stale{{/if}}">{{snapshot_google.last_review_label}}</div></td>
        <td><div class="health-dot {{snapshot_google.health_class}}">{{snapshot_google.health_label}}</div></td>
      </tr>
      {{#unless is_paid}}
      <tr>
        <td colspan="5" style="padding: 24px 0; color: var(--ink-mute); font-style: italic; text-align: center;">
          Yelp · Facebook · Zocdoc · Healthgrades — included in the paid audit.
        </td>
      </tr>
      {{/unless}}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="insight-callout">
    {{{insight_callout_html}}}
  </div>

  <div class="doc-footer">
    <span>BAAM Review Audit · {{business_name}}</span>
    <span>Page 02 / {{page_count_display}}</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ====================== PAGE 3 — SECTION 3 SCORE + DO-NOTHING ====================== -->
<section class="page">
  <header class="doc-header">
    <div class="doc-header-left">
      <div class="doc-header-brand">BAAM · Review Audit</div>
      <div class="doc-header-sub">§ 03 · Your BAAM Review Score</div>
    </div>
    <div class="doc-header-right">
      <div><strong>{{business_name}}</strong></div>
      <div>{{business_address_line_2}} · {{audit_date_display}}</div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="section-marker">
    <span class="section-marker-num">§ 03</span>
    <span class="section-marker-title">Your BAAM Review Score</span>
  </div>

  <div class="score-hero">
    <div class="score-number">{{score_total}}</div>
    <div class="score-grade-block">
      <div class="score-grade-label">Grade · Tier {{score_grade}}</div>
      <div class="score-grade-letter">{{score_grade}}</div>
      <div class="score-grade-diagnosis">{{score_grade_diagnosis}}</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-mute); margin-bottom: 14px;">Score breakdown · Why your number is what it is</div>

  <div class="subscores">
    {{#each subscore_rows}}
      {{> subscore-row}}
    {{/each}}
  </div>

  <div class="methodology-footer">
    <span class="methodology-eyebrow">METHODOLOGY</span>
    <p>Every score is measured against published vertical benchmarks. <strong>Rating Quality</strong> uses a non-linear curve that rewards the 4.0★ threshold (where 70% of consumers filter). <strong>Review Volume</strong> compares total count to the median for your vertical. <strong>Velocity</strong> scores use BAAM Review Research healthy-pace bands. The black tick marks on each bar show where these standards sit on the 0–100 scale. <a href="https://www.baamreview.com/review-value.html" target="_blank">Full methodology →</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="projection-block">
    <div class="projection-eyebrow">§ 03.5 · The Forecast</div>
    <h3 class="projection-title">Your score in <em>six months</em> if you do nothing.</h3>
    <p class="projection-deck">Three forces work against a business that stops collecting reviews: velocity decay (mechanical), ranking decline (Sterling Sky), and competitors compounding the gap. This projection holds your current effort constant — and holds your competitors at their measured pace.</p>

    <div class="projection-chart-frame">
      <div class="projection-svg-wrap">
        {{{projection_svg}}}
      </div>

      <div class="projection-legend">
        <div class="legend-item"><span class="legend-swatch red"></span> <strong>Do nothing</strong> · projected trajectory at current effort</div>
        <div class="legend-item"><span class="legend-swatch green"></span> <strong>With BAAM Review</strong> · sustained collection + response</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="projection-impact">
      <div class="impact-cell">
        <div class="impact-label">6-Month Score</div>
        <div class="impact-value">{{projection_six_month_drop_display}}</div>
        <div class="impact-sub">{{projection_floor_blurb}}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="impact-cell">
        <div class="impact-label">Ranking Position</div>
        <div class="impact-value">{{projection_ranking_drop_display}}</div>
        <div class="impact-sub">Estimated Local Pack drop · competitors compounding the gap</div>
      </div>
      <div class="impact-cell">
        <div class="impact-label">Revenue Cost</div>
        <div class="impact-value">{{projection_revenue_loss_display}}</div>
        <div class="impact-sub">6-month opportunity cost · vertical per-review value × missed reviews</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grade-scale-block">
    <div class="grade-scale-eyebrow">The full scale · where each grade sits</div>
    <h3 class="grade-scale-headline">Your <em>{{score_grade}}</em> in context — and what it would take to climb.</h3>
    <table class="grade-scale-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Score Range</th>
          <th class="center">Grade</th>
          <th>What it means in plain English</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr{{#if (eq score_grade "A")}} class="current"{{/if}}>
          <td><span class="score-range">90 – 100</span></td>
          <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade-letter-pill g-a">A</span></td>
          <td><span class="grade-meaning">Winning your local market. Reviews are a competitive moat.{{#if (eq score_grade "A")}}<span class="you-here-pill">You · {{score_total}}</span>{{/if}}</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr{{#if (eq score_grade "B")}} class="current"{{/if}}>
          <td><span class="score-range">75 – 89</span></td>
          <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade-letter-pill g-b">B</span></td>
          <td><span class="grade-meaning">Strong — but losing ground to top competitors month over month.{{#if (eq score_grade "B")}}<span class="you-here-pill">You · {{score_total}}</span>{{/if}}</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr{{#if (eq score_grade "C")}} class="current"{{/if}}>
          <td><span class="score-range">60 – 74</span></td>
          <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade-letter-pill g-c">C</span></td>
          <td><span class="grade-meaning">Visible — but customers are choosing competitors with stronger reviews.{{#if (eq score_grade "C")}}<span class="you-here-pill">You · {{score_total}}</span>{{/if}}</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr{{#if (eq score_grade "D")}} class="current"{{/if}}>
          <td><span class="score-range">40 – 59</span></td>
          <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade-letter-pill g-d">D</span></td>
          <td><span class="grade-meaning">Bleeding customers to better-reviewed competitors every week.{{#if (eq score_grade "D")}}<span class="you-here-pill">You · {{score_total}}</span>{{/if}}</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr{{#if (eq score_grade "F")}} class="current"{{/if}}>
          <td><span class="score-range">0 – 39</span></td>
          <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade-letter-pill g-f">F</span></td>
          <td><span class="grade-meaning">Effectively invisible. Search and AI are skipping you entirely.{{#if (eq score_grade "F")}}<span class="you-here-pill">You · {{score_total}}</span>{{/if}}</span></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="doc-footer">
    <span>BAAM Review Audit · {{business_name}}</span>
    <span>Page 03 / {{page_count_display}}</span>
  </div>
</section>

{{#unless is_paid}}
<!-- ====================== FREE TIER UPGRADE CTA ====================== -->
<section class="page" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; align-items: center; text-align: center;">
  <div class="section-marker" style="border-bottom: none; margin-bottom: 24px;">
    <span class="section-marker-num">§ 04+</span>
    <span class="section-marker-title">What the paid audit unlocks</span>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-headline" style="max-width: 640px;">You've seen <em>where you stand.</em><br>Now see what it costs — and what to do.</h2>

  <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 36px auto; max-width: 540px; text-align: left;">
    <li style="padding: 12px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);"><strong>Section 4 · Industry Benchmarks</strong> — your vertical's per-review dollar value, healthy velocity bands, what "top 25%" actually looks like.</li>
    <li style="padding: 12px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);"><strong>Section 5 · Competitor Comparison</strong> — your 5 closest competitors, side-by-side, with the gap quantified.</li>
    <li style="padding: 12px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);"><strong>Section 6 · 12-Month Action Plan</strong> — five concrete moves, ranked by impact, with the dollar value of each.</li>
    <li style="padding: 12px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);"><strong>Sections 1–3 · Multi-platform extension</strong> — Yelp, Facebook, Zocdoc, Healthgrades scoring blended in.</li>
    <li style="padding: 12px 0;"><strong>Section 7 · Appendix</strong> — the full reference tables.</li>
  </ul>

  <p style="font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif; font-size: 22px; font-style: italic; max-width: 580px; color: var(--ink); margin: 24px 0;">
    Every grade you saw in this report is honest about the data we had.<br>The paid audit shows you the full picture.
  </p>

  <div class="doc-footer" style="margin-top: auto;">
    <span>BAAM Review Audit · {{business_name}}</span>
    <span>Page {{page_count_display}} / {{page_count_display}}</span>
  </div>
</section>
{{/unless}}

</body>
</html>
